You probably know Next 14 came out almost a month ago.

And it caused a lot of mixed reactions.

=E2=80=8B

=E2=80=9CI just learned 13, and now I have to learn 14 =F0=9F=98=AD=E2=80=
=9D

=E2=80=9CUnsafe!=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=9CPHP!!!!=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=8B

I=E2=80=99m only writing this now since=E2=80=A6 all of those were just
overreactions.

Because basically nothing changed.

The biggest change is the number (13 =E2=86=92 14).

=E2=80=8B

Yup.

Don=E2=80=99t believe me?

Look:

=E2=80=8B
=E2=80=8B

* They made things faster.
=E2=80=8B
* Server Actions are now stable.

=E2=80=8B

=E2=80=9COh no, what the heck are Server Actions??=E2=80=9D

Simply put, Server Actions are functions that run on the server,
but that we can call from the client, just like a normal
function.

That way, you don=E2=80=99t need to build out full API routes for some
use cases.

=E2=80=8B

=E2=80=9CBut wait, does this mean your Next.js course is outdated?=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=8B

Nope.

We already used server actions in our course when it was created
with Next 13.5.

A team member joked a few months back: =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re among the onl=
y 50
people in the world who know how to use Server Actions =F0=9F=98=85=E2=80=
=9D

=E2=80=8B

Knowing something deeply pays off, even if it takes a whole lot
of time.

When you truly understand something, you don=E2=80=99t have to panic like
half the Twitter/X did. And you can stay at the cutting-edge of
tech.

=E2=80=8B

But wait, what about SQL injections?

If you know what you=E2=80=99re doing, it=E2=80=99s not a problem. Some dev=
s who
don=E2=80=99t know their stuff made a fuss, but there isn=E2=80=99t a secur=
ity
issue if you do things right.

=E2=80=8B

What about Remix and other frameworks?

I like Next and have nothing against Remix, Astro, and other
frameworks.

At the end of the day, all of these frameworks are great options.
What matters isn=E2=80=99t the syntax or the name, but true understanding
of how the web works. Deep understanding of basics rather than
memorization of concepts.

=E2=80=8B

That being said, hundreds of giants like ChatGPT, TikTok,
Starbucks, DoorDash use Next.

That=E2=80=99s one advantage Next has over other frameworks. If you=E2=80=
=99re
going to go deep in one framework, there=E2=80=99s a strong case to use
the most popular one. Or even better, the one that=E2=80=99s most aligned
with your goals, use cases, and places you want to work at.

=E2=80=8B

